In a statement on Israeli Independence Day, the President expressed his well wishes to the Israeli people. He emphasized the strong friendship and alliance between the United States and Israel, stating that it makes both countries safer, stronger, and more prosperous. The President also mentioned his visit to Israel and his time at Mount Herzl, where he paid tribute to those who played a significant role in the establishment and protection of Israel. He reaffirmed the unbreakable alliance between the two nations and their shared commitment to achieving security and peace.